A pulsing scheme with an overall 28 Hz macro-pulse structure has been selected as the baseline design, corresponding to Option A+ in Fig. 3. The pulse length in this case is limited by the flat-top length of the present RF modulators (3.35 ms). Since the filling time of the superconducting cavities is about 0.3 ms, and the time to stabilise the radio frequency (RF) regulation is about 0.1 ms, the effective pulse length is limited to about 2.9 ms. If the pulse length from the modulators could be extended, this would decrease the demand of the current. Other pulsing schemes have also been reviewed (Options B and C) where the H-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
