Moreover, a variety of metals can be coated with a sub-monolayer of Cs, to reduce the work function further than possible with solid Cs; this yields a theoretical optimum coverage of around 0.6 monolayers, having a work function of about 1.5 eV [26]. The low work function is important for an electron to be easily transferred from the cathode surface toward a hydrogen molecule to form an H-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
