 The ion source in use at ISIS, RAL, is a surface plasma ion source of Penning type, see Fig. 7 [11]. The Penning source was first developed by Dudnikov [13] and has also been used at Los Alamos National Laboratory (LANL) [27]. The Penning ion source can produce high currents, up to 100 mA, provide high-emission current densities > 1 A/cm2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
