				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\text {ESS}}\nu {\text {SB}}$$\end{document}, where the frequency is doubled between normal and superconducting linac sections. However, long-term cumulative damage from undetected double stripping “hot spots” as reported in [76] may still be a risk, and should be prevented.

