Lorentz stripping is also compounded in transfer lines. Although it is below problematic levels in the quadrupoles, in the bending dipoles, it makes a significant contribution. (The Lorentz stripping scales with the bending radius, e.g., ρ=73\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
