				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\text {ESS}}\nu {\text {SB}}$$\end{document}, and 8 new ones must be constructed, for a total of 41 modulators.

To study the performance of the present SML modulators for the new pulsing conditions of the proposed scenarios, a simulation model was developed using MATLAB Simulink [100]. First, to maintain flicker-free operation, charging power was proportionally increased with the idea of recovering the lost energy of all pulses (1 proton pulse plus 1–4 H-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
