				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\text {H}}^-$$\end{document} pulses. SML modulator pulse generation control systems were, in these cases, adjusted to compensate. The following text details the simulation results for each scenario with particular focus on (1) rise time, used in deriving modulator beam efficiency, (2) pulse flat top ripple, and (3) the dynamics of the capacitor charger waveforms.

