				\begin{document}$${\text {ESS}}\nu {\text {SB}}$$\end{document} project to address such safety issues in due time [130].

The unprecedented power of the ESS linac set the impetus to investigate the feasibility of increasing its duty cycle to be the driver for a neutrino oscillation experiment. The target and horn requirements put a limit on the final pulse length, which is obtainable only by adding an accumulator between the linac and the target. For improved injection to such an accumulator, the H-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
