The conceptual design of the injection beam dump consists of a water-cooled copper cylinder of 25 cm radius and 120 cm length, surrounded by 3 m of iron inner shielding and 1 m of concrete outer shielding. The power loss and prompt radiation levels have been calculated for a beam loss of 0.5 MW, 0.2 mA average beam, 10% beam loss. Under normal operation, a lower beam loss is expected—on the order of 2%. The power loss reaches 30 W/cm3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
