The first branch of the BSY transports and focuses the beam onto the target named “T1”. The T1 axis is the main axis of the beam upon exiting the R2S line. To reach T1, the dipoles D1 and D3 act as a drift tube. In other words, no induced magnetic field is needed from their magnets. Figure 79 shows the beam envelopes for the T1 branch. According to these simulations, this branch has a transmission of 100% and is achromatic at its extremity. The radii of the beam in the middle of the target are expected to be 14.90 mm and 14.94 mm in x and y, respectively. Table 14 presents the main beam parameters at the target location.Table 14
