The feasibility of having adequate rise and fall times for dipoles must be tested with respect to the operating frequency. Alternatively, dipoles D1, D3, and D5 could also be a combination of a kicker and a septum. Indeed, according to simulations, a pair of fast kickers of 0.5 m long each could be used to kick the beam for a total angle of 1∘\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
