 Figure 111 shows the general concept of a four-horn support frame. The proposed solution takes into account both the assembly and operation conditions. For this purpose, a frame system was proposed which provides a relatively easy access to the horns and their additional equipment (water jets, drain pipes, etc.), as well as sufficient stiffness resulting in minimum vertical deflections of the horns themselves (y-direction). In the proposed approach, each horn is directly supported on two saddle supports, which are located at positions in the z-direction that ensure equalisation of the maximal values of the bending moment distributed along the z-axis. These points are taken at z1=570mm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
