				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$50\,{\text {ms}}$$\end{document} acceptance window between muon creation and its decay. Given the number of expected interactions shown in Table 40, one can put a conservative upper bound on the number of beam muons produced per year as 10,000. In this case, the expected number of events per year in which a muon is created and the atmospheric neutrino interacts before this muon decays is 7.5×10-3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
