A pragmatic and very effective way of increasing both the octant and mass ordering sensitivity of a neutrino oscillation experiment is to combine the signal from the neutrino beam with the substantial atmospheric neutrino sample that will also be seen at the far detector [277, 278]. For ESSνSB\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
