The estimation of the physics sensitivity arising from beam events makes use of the GLoBES software [280, 281]. A water Cherenkov detector of fiducial volume 538 kt located either at a distance of 540 km or 360 km from the neutrino source, as discussed in Sect. 7, has been considered. A value of 2.7×1023\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
